Glean Platform Overview
What is Glean?

Glean is an enterprise AI platform that combines enterprise search, generative AI, knowledge management, and AI-powered assistants into a single solution. It enables organizations to securely access, discover, and interact with information across their enterprise systems using natural language queries and AI-driven insights.

Unlike traditional search tools, Glean leverages Large Language Models (LLMs) and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to provide contextual answers, summarize information, automate knowledge discovery, and support business workflows while respecting existing user permissions and access controls.

What Does Glean Do?
Glean serves as a centralized AI-powered knowledge hub that helps employees find information, generate content, and complete tasks more efficiently.

Key capabilities include:

Enterprise Search
Searches across multiple enterprise applications and data repositories from a single interface.
Retrieves documents, conversations, tickets, policies, and other organizational knowledge.
AI Assistant
Allows users to ask questions in natural language.
Generates contextual responses based on enterprise data and approved AI models.
Provides summaries, recommendations, and insights.
Knowledge Discovery
Identifies relevant documents, projects, teams, and subject matter experts.
Helps employees locate organizational knowledge quickly.
Content Generation
Creates drafts of emails, reports, meeting summaries, presentations, and other business content.
Summarizes lengthy documents and conversations.
AI Agents and Automation
Supports AI-powered agents that can perform research, gather information, and assist with business processes.
Automates repetitive knowledge-based tasks and workflows.
Personalized Experience
Delivers results tailored to a user's role, permissions, and organizational context.
